I’d like to share some feedback regarding the way prerelease sign-ups are currently being handled. As it stands, players are able to register for the prerelease event, not participate in the tournament itself, and still keep their prerelease bundle to pick up at a later time. While I understand the desire to accommodate different schedules and make sure players receive product, this system has some unintended consequences.

When players register but choose not to attend the event, they occupy spots that could have gone to participants who genuinely want to play in the prerelease tournament. This creates frustration for players who miss out on the experience due to limited seating. A prerelease is meant to be a community-focused event where people come together to enjoy new cards in a fun and welcoming environment. Allowing product to be reserved without participating shifts the focus away from that communal experience and instead treats the prerelease primarily as early product access.

A more balanced approach might be to separate tournament registration from product availability — for example, offering prerelease kits for pick-up after the main events have concluded, or creating a dedicated product-only option that does not affect player seating. That way, those who want to play in the prerelease can secure a spot, and those who simply want the product can still purchase it without impacting event participation.

I believe a change like this would help preserve the spirit of prerelease events, keep them accessible for players who want to enjoy the tournament experience, and still ensure everyone has access to product in a fair way.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We appreciate your feedback, but please understand that we are just following the policies set by the card companies. Unfortunately, there is never a way to force someone to play in the event - no matter what the policy is. We do prioritize in-store play for product allocation when possible. We hope that maybe you can also recognize that a one-star rating is very harmful to our small business, and we are doing our best to accommodate the wide variety of customers interested in our products and events.

reviews_data.review_text:
This store makes reading & collecting comics a genuine joy. For context, I used to collect the volumes/paperbacks of some of my favorites growing up but fell off due to school/finances around 2017. I got back into comics within the last couple of years with the idea to collect issues but it’s sometimes hard to keep up, know what’s good, where to start, what stories connect, etc.

The first time I visited the store was a while ago when I was trying to catch up on Batman. While the store doesn’t carry back issues per se, they will go out of their way to supply you with what they have. I’ll never forget walking out of the store with a huge smile on my face after Jeremy handed me issue after issue to help me catch up to speed on a storyline I had shown interest in with a previous issue I found at another LCS.  That visit left a lasting impression.

Fast forward to today, I just moved within the area and wanted to go back and check out the new location. While there, I also decided to subscribe to multiple series that I have fun collecting and reading. Jeremy was there once again and made what is sometimes an overwhelming process super easy. He walked me through the store, told me how things work, showed me where to go for the books I was interested in, and helped get me in and out as efficiently as possible. While subbing, he also informed me of cool benefits you have with being a patron which include them adding crossover events (or anything major regarding a certain story line) to your pulls which was a HUGE perk to me as sometimes I completely miss what relates to what. I am a casual as in I mainly collect and read but am not super knowledgeable how they work in regards to crossovers, big events, etc. so having Jeremy there as a trusty ally is incredibly helpful as someone who is ignorant but loves the books.

As I went in to pick up for the first time, Jeremy had my order ready before I even walked in the door. I wasstunned. Not only could I not believe I was remembered but that he was able to pull out my books that quickly. Jeremy truly does value anyone who walks through those doors and is a customer service hero. He even went back and found me an issue of Spider-Boy I was wanting while I was there that wasn’t on the wall.

Finally, the reason why I wanted to write this review is an interaction I had yesterday. I was listening to the Off Panel podcast and gained instant FOMO when I got to the episode about the Absolute series from DC. I wrote in a request to add Superman & Batman if possible. When I initially signed up I noticed he wrote it down via pen and paper so I was anxious about causing someone who’s been so helpful more work just because I was ignorant on what the Absolute series was. Not only was he able to add them, I am picking up my first issue today (to the series I subscribed to yesterday) and he even offered to reorder a Superman to make sure I could have it.

Jeremy genuinely is a Superman of this community and it is an extreme honor and privilege to be a new subscriber. I can not express how amazing this place is. Don’t be fooled, what they lack in size and back issues they more than make up for with customer service. My old LCS was Heroes Aren’t Hard to Find in Charlotte (which is also great) where I usually feel overwhelmed by the volume there and felt like just another dude but Jeremy treats me as if I am the most important customer he has despite there obviously being plenty others. Please support this business and please come visit. You absolutely will not regret it.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Jordan, thank you so much for finding our store and taking the time to write this thoughtful review. We are so glad that our hard work is appreciated. We opened almost 15 years ago with the goal of providing the must personalized customer service possible. We never wanted to be "big"; we just wanted to know everyone's name and make sure you know you are important to us!

reviews_data.review_text:
Been going here for a while. I’m a subscriber and even left a good review four months ago. Always had a good experience picking up my comics on Wednesdays. For privacy, I won’t mention names, but the guy behind the counter is simply amazing and very knowledgeable and made everyone that comes in the door, welcomed!

However the five other times I have gone in to pick up my books or browse for new comics, I realize not everyone is on par as my guy on Wednesday mornings.

Today was the last straw… I know this guy today never asks for my name to add the comics I have purchased on days I am not picking up a pool. Never says hello or interacts. I’m not asking a lot but a hello would be cool or even asking if I have an account so he can log the comic I purchased. My old comic book stores in Raleigh and Atlanta did this and my guy on Wednesday does it too.

The store was full and had a good crowd playing card games. I saw this kid was behind the counter and was busy. So I browse like I normally do, saying hello, was ignored, found a book and started to check out. However a guest got in front of me and I figured no worries I’m usually patient. Then I realize he continued to help another two people which I probably figured were there before me so I waited again and this time I decided to “line up” behind the two people.

After five minutes, two other people walk in and the two in front of me finished, but as I move up to the register this kid goes on to help the other two that walked in. So I walked out and decided to drive to another comic book store out of the area, and guess what? I got a better welcome…

Treat and everyone the same, please. Still a nice store but I guess I’m just not the right fit or something.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Mark, we are really sorry that you had this experience. We strive to provide friendly, personalized service, and we recently had a staffing shake-up that we are in the process of resolving. We'll make it right for you!

reviews_data.review_text: Great.

I think this place sells resealed booster boxes of Pokémon cards.

My fiancé and I stopped by to grab a booster box from the new Pokémon set that just dropped and my first red flag, was that the packs looked like they sat in the sun for a long time. The font on the back of the booster packs looked really off, as well. The booster packs themselves did not look right to me, we even compared them to another booster pack we got from a different store and the packs from this place looked extremely off.

When opening the packs, everything looked correct, but I noticed that we weren’t getting as many hits from this box compared to the other one. I know that it’s all luck of the draw, but this new set has nothing but hits to it.

Be wary when purchasing booster boxes from this place.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We can tell you 100% that all of our Pokemon product is factory-sealed. If you have any issues with Pokemon product, you should absolutely report it to the Pokemon Company. We do NOT do any of these things that your are unfairly accusing us of. We have many families and customers who regular purchase sealed Pokemon products from us, and no one has ever complained. We don't even sell Pokemon singles, so there wouldn't even be any incentive for us to "repack" product.

I’d like to share some feedback regarding the way prerelease sign-ups are currently being handled. As it stands, players are able to register for the prerelease event, not participate in the tournament itself, and still keep their prerelease bundle to pick up at a later time. While I understand the desire to accommodate different schedules and make sure players receive product, this system has some unintended consequences.

When players register but choose not to attend the event, they occupy spots that could have gone to participants who genuinely want to play in the prerelease tournament. This creates frustration for players who miss out on the experience due to limited seating. A prerelease is meant to be a community-focused event where people come together to enjoy new cards in a fun and welcoming environment. Allowing product to be reserved without participating shifts the focus away from that communal experience and instead treats the prerelease primarily as early product access.

A more balanced approach might be to separate tournament registration from product availability — for example, offering prerelease kits for pick-up after the main events have concluded, or creating a dedicated product-only option that does not affect player seating. That way, those who want to play in the prerelease can secure a spot, and those who simply want the product can still purchase it without impacting event participation.

I believe a change like this would help preserve the spirit of prerelease events, keep them accessible for players who want to enjoy the tournament experience, and still ensure everyone has access to product in a fair way.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We appreciate your feedback, but please understand that we are just following the policies set by the card companies. Unfortunately, there is never a way to force someone to play in the event - no matter what the policy is. We do prioritize in-store play for product allocation when possible. We hope that maybe you can also recognize that a one-star rating is very harmful to our small business, and we are doing our best to accommodate the wide variety of customers interested in our products and events.

reviews_data.review_text:
This store makes reading & collecting comics a genuine joy. For context, I used to collect the volumes/paperbacks of some of my favorites growing up but fell off due to school/finances around 2017. I got back into comics within the last couple of years with the idea to collect issues but it’s sometimes hard to keep up, know what’s good, where to start, what stories connect, etc.

The first time I visited the store was a while ago when I was trying to catch up on Batman. While the store doesn’t carry back issues per se, they will go out of their way to supply you with what they have. I’ll never forget walking out of the store with a huge smile on my face after Jeremy handed me issue after issue to help me catch up to speed on a storyline I had shown interest in with a previous issue I found at another LCS.  That visit left a lasting impression.

Fast forward to today, I just moved within the area and wanted to go back and check out the new location. While there, I also decided to subscribe to multiple series that I have fun collecting and reading. Jeremy was there once again and made what is sometimes an overwhelming process super easy. He walked me through the store, told me how things work, showed me where to go for the books I was interested in, and helped get me in and out as efficiently as possible. While subbing, he also informed me of cool benefits you have with being a patron which include them adding crossover events (or anything major regarding a certain story line) to your pulls which was a HUGE perk to me as sometimes I completely miss what relates to what. I am a casual as in I mainly collect and read but am not super knowledgeable how they work in regards to crossovers, big events, etc. so having Jeremy there as a trusty ally is incredibly helpful as someone who is ignorant but loves the books.

As I went in to pick up for the first time, Jeremy had my order ready before I even walked in the door. I wasstunned. Not only could I not believe I was remembered but that he was able to pull out my books that quickly. Jeremy truly does value anyone who walks through those doors and is a customer service hero. He even went back and found me an issue of Spider-Boy I was wanting while I was there that wasn’t on the wall.

Finally, the reason why I wanted to write this review is an interaction I had yesterday. I was listening to the Off Panel podcast and gained instant FOMO when I got to the episode about the Absolute series from DC. I wrote in a request to add Superman & Batman if possible. When I initially signed up I noticed he wrote it down via pen and paper so I was anxious about causing someone who’s been so helpful more work just because I was ignorant on what the Absolute series was. Not only was he able to add them, I am picking up my first issue today (to the series I subscribed to yesterday) and he even offered to reorder a Superman to make sure I could have it.

Jeremy genuinely is a Superman of this community and it is an extreme honor and privilege to be a new subscriber. I can not express how amazing this place is. Don’t be fooled, what they lack in size and back issues they more than make up for with customer service. My old LCS was Heroes Aren’t Hard to Find in Charlotte (which is also great) where I usually feel overwhelmed by the volume there and felt like just another dude but Jeremy treats me as if I am the most important customer he has despite there obviously being plenty others. Please support this business and please come visit. You absolutely will not regret it.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Jordan, thank you so much for finding our store and taking the time to write this thoughtful review. We are so glad that our hard work is appreciated. We opened almost 15 years ago with the goal of providing the must personalized customer service possible. We never wanted to be "big"; we just wanted to know everyone's name and make sure you know you are important to us!

Been going here for a while. I’m a subscriber and even left a good review four months ago. Always had a good experience picking up my comics on Wednesdays. For privacy, I won’t mention names, but the guy behind the counter is simply amazing and very knowledgeable and made everyone that comes in the door, welcomed!

However the five other times I have gone in to pick up my books or browse for new comics, I realize not everyone is on par as my guy on Wednesday mornings.

Today was the last straw… I know this guy today never asks for my name to add the comics I have purchased on days I am not picking up a pool. Never says hello or interacts. I’m not asking a lot but a hello would be cool or even asking if I have an account so he can log the comic I purchased. My old comic book stores in Raleigh and Atlanta did this and my guy on Wednesday does it too.

The store was full and had a good crowd playing card games. I saw this kid was behind the counter and was busy. So I browse like I normally do, saying hello, was ignored, found a book and started to check out. However a guest got in front of me and I figured no worries I’m usually patient. Then I realize he continued to help another two people which I probably figured were there before me so I waited again and this time I decided to “line up” behind the two people.

After five minutes, two other people walk in and the two in front of me finished, but as I move up to the register this kid goes on to help the other two that walked in. So I walked out and decided to drive to another comic book store out of the area, and guess what? I got a better welcome…

Treat and everyone the same, please. Still a nice store but I guess I’m just not the right fit or something.

I think this place sells resealed booster boxes of Pokémon cards.

My fiancé and I stopped by to grab a booster box from the new Pokémon set that just dropped and my first red flag, was that the packs looked like they sat in the sun for a long time. The font on the back of the booster packs looked really off, as well. The booster packs themselves did not look right to me, we even compared them to another booster pack we got from a different store and the packs from this place looked extremely off.

When opening the packs, everything looked correct, but I noticed that we weren’t getting as many hits from this box compared to the other one. I know that it’s all luck of the draw, but this new set has nothing but hits to it.

Be wary when purchasing booster boxes from this place.

Great ice cream and helpful staff
Pleasant service!
Great
Cool spot for comics enthusiasts. If they expanded their selections, it'd be even better. Ice cream was very good.
Always very nice staff
Great selection
Interesting and new for me
Icecream is delicious!!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We're glad you liked the ice cream! How do we earn two more stars from you?

reviews_data.review_text: This is a quaint comic book shop for the neighborhood and community that it serves. I have no complaints with it the customer service on Parr is very engaging.
Friendly staff and they wore masks 😷

Super cool local spot that is a bit under the radar. Comics, games, and ice cream. Weekly tournament and game nights. The folks here are always friendly and helpful. Definitely worth stopping by if you're in the area.
Lovely little place with excellent service and good selection.
I've been going ever since I was six and they have never disappoint.
Friendly staff - games on site... And ice cream!
Great staff, friendly environment.
Super friendly staff, non-judgemental atmosphere and just all around nice place to hang out.

Awesome place!! My 9 year old really likes Pokemon but no nearby kids play. Found this spot on the internet. The owner himself showed my kid the ropes of the game. Free play session is well run also. 👍🏽👍🏽👍🏽
Neat
So much fun!!  Pokemon was played, conversations had, smiles provided, and a spot of ice cream.
Selection limited, hard to find issues

Definitely love coming here every week for a good ol' DnD session. Always fun and everyone knows everyone, we're just just a big friend group. The atmosphere is great the selection of stuff they have is great. They have DnD every Wednesday from 7-9 and you can always come early and hang in the store. I love going early with my friend and getting some rounds of MTG in before the night starts.
Very, Very, nice staff. Had a great visit, worth 40 minute drive to get there for me.
We love this local shop and DnD nights!
Spandex City is a fabulous comic book store. The personnel is nice and knowledgeable, really helpful, and they organize tons of super cool events. Ivery much recommend it!
Great place for tabletop gaming!!  Jeremy and Mike and crew are amazing!  Super family friendly!
Not a large selection of comics, but the ice cream is good though.
Great atmosphere and staff. Every organized event I've gone to has gone above and beyond to ensure their players have a great time.
I go here every time for the Pokémon League and it is an amazing place to be. Amazing service and great community. And they even have ice cream :3
Nice place.

The people at this place are just FANTASTIC. So friendly, and super knowledgeable. We love taking our Pokemon Team to events here. Love the fact that I can get ice cream here, and sit out on the bench and enjoy the weather. They have some great flavors of ice cream- my favorite is butter pecan.
Nice local shop.
Best icecream ever!
Great customer service! We came in looking for mtg land cards and they gave us some for free because they had extra. They do weekly tournaments,  and the Saturday ones are free to enter
Spandex city is THE comic book store in west Charlotte. Very polite people, always a joy to visit. Jeremy and Victoria both get 👍👍.
I took my nephew in to get some ice cream and the guy, with no  gloves on took a spoon got him a spoonful of it. He didn't wash his hands or anything. We didn't get the icecream.
Friendly customers and staff
This was my first time here. It was not at all what I was expecting but I was pleasantly surprised. The cashier was very nice and knowledgeable. He has secured a customer for life!
I always have an awesome time with Mike and the staff.

I love this place. I havent been for years but recently went back for a magic prerelease and felt like I was right back at home. Everyone who works here treats you like a friend. Every event is ran professionally. I constantly reccomend it to people for comics or magic.
Great service, very friendly staff, and great atmosphere
Cool little comic store. My son loves coming here to browse the action figures and play the games.
Great selection and awesome ice cream shop, a seating area to enjoy ice cream play games or read your comics. Excellent customerservice.
Love this place the workers are so nice and it a has really good vibe.
Knowledgeable staff. Great MTG crowd and awesome comic selection.
Love the shakes and enjoy being there for the magic events and absolutely love there display
Love this store

I love love love this comic book shop.  I just hate that it's so far away from my house.  I got comics there for a long time and everyone there was really helpful and knowledgeable and just generally interested in storylines you were interested in.  If I lived a little closer I'd be there all the time.
Overall fun place to go look/buy Comic Books, Boardgames, Card Games etc. Would highly recommend checking it out.
Nice spot.  Son loves the comic book place...Pokemon tournaments.

This store has some of the friendliest staff I've met.  My wife has limited knowledge of comic books and they made sure to spend time with her educating and recommending books to start out on based off her interests.

Will definitely continue to support!
Great hidden place find it and enjoy yourself with their amazing comics and ice cream
Great people, excellent place to play and hang
They have killer shakes and ice cream sodas here. Plus my kids love their comic selection.

This place has been extremely welcoming. Everyone I met so far has been amazingly helpful and the people that work here are ready to help you learn any game that they run. This place is highly recommended for any trading card game, or table top rpg that they run

This is a fun little comic book store. They have ice cream, pin ball machines, magic and pokemon cards, comics, board games, and even some action figure and comic themed items that are fun to see.

Check their schedule for magic tournaments and Pokemon tournaments. They are a great place to hang out and have fun.
Has lots of cool stuff great place to chill and eat ice cream
Ice cream and magic the gathering two great combinations. Small shop, small MTG turn out, and limited MTG resources. Not a bad place to play casually.
Great place to take kids. Lots of gaming space and newer comics. No back issue bins but a nice place and nice staff.... also... pinball machines.
If you come to play an official Pokémon tournament they don’t have an official judge
Loved it.  Good selection of comics and they have ice cream.
Very fun and cozy store
Not a comic book store.
Halfway decent selection, nice people. Maybe not the place to look for more obscure collector pieces, but they have the stock superheroes covered.
They have something for everyone here!!! We really enjoyed our first experience and plan to return over and over again!

Smaller shop with a blend of games and comics. Mostly current issues with a small population of trades. Games play more to the favorites and there a few tables out for community play. The ice cream looked good.
We go to play limited MTG mostly. Travel 45min, past several other shops to enjoy the atmosphere and low key vibe. Casual friendly.
No greeting upon entering and some of the tables were cluttered with business papers. Ice cream was good.
Friendly staff, cool concept for a shop. Really liked the game portion of the store and the comic grab bags. They also have ice cream here. I'd like more old issues, but I'm old school like that.

Great comic book store. They also have card game items. Operators are incredibly nice. My son enjoys going here for the Pokémon TCG battles. The other customers we've met have all been friendly as well!
Dont say bad thing about this place...😎
Great store! Fantastic milkshakes 😘
My girls love this place.  Ice cream, pinball, and comics.  Great shop.  Go visit them.

I dropped by to play Magic for one of the Saturday Standard Showdowns (free entry!). I loved the store. The shop was a little small compared to the others I have been to, but the staff was excellent and attentive organizing the tournament. They also have ice cream so I got a cherry soda float which was awesome. Bring a play mat if you come to play cards, and their selection of singles is very limited, but they are desirable cards. I plan to visit again.
Great place to get comics and ice cream. The spinners are my favorite and I love to play pinball while having my ice cream and comics.

Comics, board games, card games, paraphernalia of all types ... whats not to love. They have card game tournaments and pinball machines. Did I mention they have ice cream, shakes, and floats? A fun place for kids of all ages.

The staff was quite rude. The selection was subpar. A lot was left to be desired namely air conditioning and even slightly competent staff. They made me pay a "convenience fee" for a shopping experience that was anything but convenient. Over all I hope more than anything that I can make good choices in life that will never bring me to such a horrible store.
One of the best comic shops in Charlotte. Family friendly, plenty of events for everyone and an amazingly friendly staff. Could not recommend more!
Great place for comics, pinball and ice cream.
Great place for the kids to play Pokemon! Staff is super understanding and helpful.
Excellent place to play Pokemon or Magic.
Great staff & great environment.

Always helpful, friendly, and willing to chat about comics. Not pushy with sales but will go the extra mile - for example offering to add other linked books to a current sub if they’re integral to the main story, so you get the whole experience of the event. This is the way small businesses should be run, I will definitely support with my money in the future
What a comic book store should be
Friendly atmosphere.  Everyone was willing and able to help.  Great place for beginners

Smaller stock of comics here, not many TPB’s or Hardcovers, but great selection of Absolute Editions. No Pops. Picked up Absolute Dark Knight, which made my night. Mostly a gaming store. Friendly staff, well decorated interior and very clean and new. Oh, and there’s ice cream. Worth visiting.
They take the time to know their customers. Magic events are fun and have good prize support.
I've been going here for years. I love this place.

Been going here for almost 4 years now. Great people working here. They take the time to learn your name. They always are able to order any new books I want in the future. They keep me up to date with any new titles I may be interested in. When they do special events and are giving out free products the owner has made sure to give me products that he knows I will be interested in. The ice cream is great. Even though I don't play the card games everyone who does play them really seem to be enjoying themselves when I happen to come by on their game days. If you want a nice family friendly environment, or just want to go in and grab the newest books available, I definitely recommend checking out this store.
GR8 place to visit every time I stop by makes me want to go back again.
Really cool place.
Cool little store just not enough comics seems as though they get only a few of each new comic book that come out

The staff at Spandex City Comics are outstanding they're right there ready to help you any way they can.
For instance on my last visit I bought two Heroclix that I collect, the ones I got I didn't want but one of the employees did he had bought some before work and let me trade for the two I wanted. Thanks man!!
Great place!  Wish they had bigger tables.
My 10 yr old enjoys Pokemon play time and meeting all aged players. Prices for play time and items for sale very reasonable. They also have ice cream.
It's is a quaint comic book store. They have a couple of pin ball machines. They hold different tournaments. Friendly staff and best of all they serve ice cream and shakes!
I went with my two sons to get Pokemon cards and the gentleman there working was very helpful we will definitely go again
Combination comic and ice cream shop is pretty dope. Owner was nice and accommodating to various requests I had during a 9 hour magic tournament.
Very clean and vibrant shop...needs more table space
Love this place. Very friendly environment. Jeremy does a good job running the magic events.  Spandex is my favorite place  to play magic the gathering. The ice cream is great as well.

I have been going to FCBD (free comic book day) every year for quite some time.  Typically I buy my comics, figures, games, etc online but it's nice to go out and support local shops every once and a while too. I just moved to the area down here in NC, and I was looking for a Comic Shop locally to perhaps purchase from every once and a while...with FCBD being a test day to see how it went. At first I thought this place was awesome!  Unlike some people, I also buy items on FCBD as well to make sure the store gets a little money out of a day when tons of free stuff is given away.  Unfortunately, the store places GIANT STICKERS ON THEIR COMICS...IMPOSSIBLE TO GET OFF AND IT DESTROYED EVERYONE OF THE COMICS THAT I GOT TODAY.  I was so extremely careful trying to remove them as well.  I tried to peel it off on some, and on others I tried using a hair-dryer to get the adhesive to melt a little...no dice.  They were all ruined.  I would have left the stickers on if they were smaller, but they were giant stickers and they covered the artwork...WHY???? NEVER SHOPPING HERE AGAIN...lol, even when the items are for free, I wont be shopping here.

Although it did look like a nice shop I didn't like the organization. Also called about a book and the girl on the phone said they had it and would hold. Drove 30 mins out of the way to get to the store and find out they didn't have it. Very dissapointing and have not been back since.
If you want comics this might be the place for you. If it's games or anything else, don't bother.
My son loves coming here to play Pokémon TCG!
Great Superhero Comic shop and more

Was an OK comic shop. I felt like it was more for the casual collector/reader as they had no back stock and only had comics from the past month or so. The person working was very nice but again the store is more for talking about comics than the comics themself. The comics took up around 20% of the store and that's counting trades. The rest was board games, toys, and the ice cream parlor. Still a nice place to go.
It's a pokestop!
Great comics & a lot of fun family friendly activities!

The staff was very friendly. We had a good time playing the pinball machines, perusing the comics and games. The staff tried to warn us that the "Superman" ice-cream was very different and we didn't listen. Our daughter didn't like it. Not their fault we didn't listen, they tried.
Fun and knowledgeable staff and also pin ball!
I love comics! They are amazing people and great atmosphere! I support my local comic shop.
4 pin ball machines, ice cream, comics and more...
Great place for comics. Definitely a good hang out spot for kids and adults and welcomes a friendly, fun environment.

Staff not very friendly.  Stop by with my kids for ice-cream and I think the two ladies need to work on "customer service."  As a local shop, I would think the owner would appreciate the business coming in....did not feel like they did today.

Good staff and friendly.  Second time here for mtg prerelease tournament.  Not likely to return, though, as they don't allow you to bring drinks of any kind. Bad idea when your customers are going to be there for 4 hours or more. Trying to make a forced buck on soda sales to a captured audience is tacky to say the least.
Great shopping experience!! Very nice store!
Great staff! Both my son and I learned how to play Pokémon here. Looking forward to meeting more folks and playing in the leagues.

I have no beef with this store.  They have a decent mix of comics, games and collectibles and while it isn't huge, they had some good stuff.  As I went on a Saturday, they had some kind of tournament going on so seems to be good for kids, too.  I was looking for Munchkin expansions specifically and while they didn't have the one I wanted, they had more than a few.

This is a great store with excellent, friendly customer service all the time.  No, they don't have too many back issues but they will order them for you if you ask.  You can also go on their website and preorder whatever you want. They really focus on new comics, the subscription service and the lounge where they host games. You don't have to pay extra for bags and boards & they have incentives and discounts for repeat customers. I can't say enough good things about Spandex City.
Pretty little comic store. New comics and a few collectibles. Not an authentic old school shop though. They don't carry back issues beyond 5 or 6 months.

The store has a friendly feel with a good mixture of game activities and comics.  There are Pokémon camps for younger players and a variety of other game events for both adults and teens including Heroclix and Friday Night Magic.  The staff is friendly and knowledgeable and the owners are helpful and can find just about anything you want ordered.  Great neighborhood entertainments option with people who love the hobbies as much as their customers.

The owners are great people and treat their customers excellent. They spend extra time and attention to my daughter which is very nice since she does not read comics. The selection is nice and the account/comic hold system is great. The only real negative is that they do not have older comics and only deal in new product as far as I can tell. A++++ store and ownership!

The layout of the store is fantastic, and the owner is really interactive with his customers. I only wish I had more money for all the great things he has available. His selection is hands down one of the best I've see outside of online retailer. Thanks for the great interaction, if I'm ever in town again I'll be sure to stop by.
